  <summary>3/17/2005--Introduced.
Volunteer Responder Incentive Protection Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income and to exempt from social security, unemployment taxes, and withholding of tax requirements rebates of real or personal property taxes or any other benefit provided by a State or local government to a member of a volunteer emergency response organization providing firefighting or emergency medical services.</summary>
